Step 1: Download Dataset 1

            Download the Bot_IoT Dataset from the following link:  
            https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/vigneshvenkateswaran/bot-iot 

Step 2: Download Dataset 2 

            Download the CIFAR-10 Dataset from the following link:  
            https://www.cs.toronto.edu/~kriz/cifar.html

Step 3: Download Dataset 3 

            Download the CoAt–Set (Coordinated Attack Dataset) from the following link:  
            https://data.mendeley.com/datasets/28tmfg3rzb/2

Step 4: Preprocessing

             Before using any dataset, ensure it is preprocessed properly.

Step 5: Open the Python Application  

            Navigate to the project folder named:  
            final_code  

Step 6: Open the Main Script  
 
            Open the files:  
            main.py  and test.py

Step 7: Load the Dataset  

            When prompted:  
            - Enter the full path to the dataset file (e.g., a CSV file)  
            - Enter the name of the label column from the dataset  

Step 8: Run the Application  

            Execute the main script:
             main.py

Step 9: View the Output  

            After execution, the model will display the performance results such as:
            Accuracy, Precision, Recall F1-Score, Specificity, AUC-ROC, Latency (ms), QoS, Throughput and Data Privacy.

Step 10: Repeat for All Datasets  

             Repeat Steps 4 to 10 for each of the three datasets to complete the full evaluation.
